06/12/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- One soldier was killed and another one was injured in a clash with members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in southeast Turkey on Friday (December 4th).
It happened during an operation against the PKK near the village of Dibek, in Mardin province.
Also Friday, two people were injured in a bombing near a park in the southern city of Adana.
Both men are in hospital in stable condition.
(Xinhua, Press TV, Anadolu news agency, AFP - 04/12/09)
